title: Outliers Turkey, Hungary threaten NATO unity in standoff with Russia
description: As the alliance prepares to gather in Lithuania for a critical summit, Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan and Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban are holding up Sweden’s accession.

title: Tbilisi Pride canceled after far-right mob storms festival
description: Organizers of Tbilisi Pride — which was held on a private, registration-only basis — condemned Georgian police after an anti-LGBTQ mob attacked the festival.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Moscow calls Azov commanders’ return a violation; Biden faces a divided NATO
description: Russia said the decision to transfer the five Mariupol commanders back home from Turkey directly violated an existing prisoner exchange agreement.

title: Ukraine pushes to reclaim Bakhmut fighting on fallen city’s flanks
description: Ukrainian soldiers are fighting to reclaim the captured city in the eastern Donetsk region, and reverse Russia's one significant territorial gain in the war this year.

title: ‘Why did this happen?’: Israel’s raid on Jenin, through the eyes of one family
description: For families in the Jenin refugee camp, last week’s Israeli military operation was 44 hours of terror. Few suffered the range of horrors endured by the Shiblys.

title: Yellen hails modest gains in economic talks with Chinese leaders
description: Treasury Secretary Janet L. Yellen said she pressed senior Chinese leaders about their treatment of U.S. companies during her trip to Beijing.
